The Senator representing Kogi West, Dino Melaye says he will kick out the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the November governorship election in the state if given the ticket of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Senator Melaye who obtained his expression of interest and nomination forms at the PDP national secretariat yesterday in Abuja, told newsmen that  his administration would rebuild and re-focus the economy of the state if given the mandate. He argued that he was the most experienced and qualified person for the job, adding that the PDP would dislodge the APC in the state because the state governor, Yahaya Bello did not perform. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He lamented the security situation, state of the economy, non-payment of salaries and other issues in the state, adding that he would fix the state if elected. “I am here to fix Kogi, we will bring back hope and unity among the people of Kogi State. We have passion for the people. “It’s not my ambition but the ambition of the people. The governor has not completed any single project in the state. We are ready to rebuilt the state,” he said. Kogi Guber: Dino Melaye picks forms, vows to kick out APC, Yahaya Bello Dino’s entry into Kogi gov’ship race poses new challenge for Bello I remain in PDP, says Senator Dino Melaye Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin